1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,130
Good morning and welcome. I'm pleased to report I got back from a few days of encouragement and rest at the beginning of last week.

2
00:00:10,270 --> 00:00:18,830
I was privileged to represent you as one of our leading churches in our region at a conference for pastors of the leading churches

3
00:00:18,830 --> 00:00:24,730
to gather and to just put our heads together and learn and just have collegial fellowship.

4
00:00:25,550 --> 00:00:26,670
And I got some rest.

5
00:00:26,710 --> 00:00:27,570
It was really great.

6
00:00:27,730 --> 00:00:30,790
But somehow I still picked up whatever my kids are spreading around.

7
00:00:30,910 --> 00:00:32,370
So I'm a pseudofed head today.

8
00:00:33,110 --> 00:00:36,130
And if I just sort of stare off into space, it's all right.

9
00:00:36,210 --> 00:00:37,230
I'm coming back.

10
00:00:39,040 --> 00:00:41,160
But at that conference, I do want to share this.

11
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:48,620
Our regional executive, one of our members here, Dale Salico, challenged us last morning.

12
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:56,100
And he challenged us with this reality that I want you to hear and really take in this morning because it's really impacting me.

13
00:00:56,100 --> 00:01:00,560
Dale and his estimation of where our culture is

14
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,680
and where the church is in relation to that

15
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:07,040
and the impact the church is making in our world today in North America

16
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:12,580
and his estimation is that we have somewhere between 7 and 8 years

17
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:15,100
to make major impact

18
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:19,810
or we're going to slide just like Europe into a very secular society

19
00:01:19,810 --> 00:01:24,620
and that is consistent with my own study and my own reading

20
00:01:24,620 --> 00:01:27,420
and my own studying our culture and what's happening.

21
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:30,000
That puts us out about 2010.

22
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:36,080
We have from now to 2010 to really impact the world around us

23
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:39,880
or a whole generation is going to slide right away from the gospel

24
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:41,440
and reject it all.

25
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:43,870
And that's depressing to me.

26
00:01:45,220 --> 00:01:48,460
The church is alive and well in South America.

27
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:51,680
The church is alive and well in Africa.

28
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:54,680
The church is alive and well in Southeast Asia

29
00:01:54,680 --> 00:02:00,580
and other places in the world, but North America and Europe, we are on a swift decline, and

30
00:02:00,580 --> 00:02:04,860
it's time that we as the church say, Lord, use us.

31
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:12,280
We are ready to take this culture by storm and to bring your Holy Spirit into lives of

32
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:14,240
people that so desperately need you.

33
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:19,320
And so Dale said to us pastors, basically it is not business as usual.

34
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:21,660
It is now a mission.

35
00:02:21,860 --> 00:02:23,420
We are on red alert.

36
00:02:23,420 --> 00:02:28,520
go forth and serve and transform your communities.

37
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:32,170
And I said, all right, we'll do that.

38
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:35,560
And I'm proud to say that as a leading church in our region

39
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:39,120
that we have established ourselves ready and poised to do that.

40
00:02:39,620 --> 00:02:41,520
And so I want to encourage you with that and say

41
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,820
that I think one of the ways we'll do that

42
00:02:43,820 --> 00:02:47,960
is by utilizing our spiritual gifts.

43
00:02:48,850 --> 00:02:52,790
When we discover what God has designed us for

44
00:02:52,790 --> 00:02:55,670
and made and hardwired us for.

45
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:59,280
We will serve with the power of the Holy Spirit

46
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:01,420
through those giftings.

47
00:03:01,660 --> 00:03:02,860
We'll change the world.

48
00:03:03,910 --> 00:03:05,970
I look forward to seeing how he's going to do that

49
00:03:05,970 --> 00:03:07,330
as we discover these gifts.

50
00:03:07,770 --> 00:03:09,270
So now we are in our second week

51
00:03:09,270 --> 00:03:11,950
as we study the issue of spiritual gifts.

52
00:03:12,590 --> 00:03:13,930
For those of you this morning

53
00:03:13,930 --> 00:03:16,090
that might be new to God's kingdom,

54
00:03:16,770 --> 00:03:19,710
perhaps you are new in a relationship with Jesus,

55
00:03:20,330 --> 00:03:22,250
and you are sitting there this morning

56
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:24,090
and you're just excited.

57
00:03:24,870 --> 00:03:26,350
I mean, life is new.

58
00:03:26,530 --> 00:03:28,150
You are cleansed and forgiven

59
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:30,650
and you are raring to go.

60
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,340
And you have been forgiven of your past.

61
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:39,080
The future is totally open and in front of you.

62
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,180
And you are looking forward to launching

63
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:42,560
into a new kind of life.

64
00:03:42,940 --> 00:03:44,300
You want to make a difference.

65
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:46,420
You want your life to count.

66
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,000
What do you do next?

67
00:03:49,870 --> 00:03:51,370
What do you do next?

68
00:03:51,810 --> 00:03:54,950
And that, I hope, we will answer this morning.

69
00:03:56,970 --> 00:04:00,470
Or, you may have been a Christian for quite some time.

70
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:08,040
You may have been sitting in church for years, perhaps decades,

71
00:04:08,620 --> 00:04:14,450
and you've got a lot of great teaching and information under your belt.

72
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:18,370
You have sat under some of the best teachers and preachers

73
00:04:18,370 --> 00:04:21,310
that this church and other churches have had to offer,

74
00:04:21,310 --> 00:04:26,670
and you are really knowledgeable of the scriptures and raring to go.

75
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:35,770
But still, when you serve in the church, you still don't feel deeply fulfilled.

76
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:42,640
You're not sure that what you're doing really connects with the community

77
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:46,880
or even perhaps what God made you to be about.

78
00:04:47,340 --> 00:04:50,660
You know this, and you know yourself,

79
00:04:50,660 --> 00:05:00,400
but you're not sure that what you're doing and serving is really humming on all the cylinders that it could be.

80
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:05,200
And you're asking yourself, am I really in a good fit?

81
00:05:05,860 --> 00:05:11,840
Does what I do really contribute and get the ball down the field in terms of the mission of this church?

82
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:16,980
Am I really making a difference for God's kingdom?

83
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:24,310
And if you're asking that question today, we've also got some answers for you.

84
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:32,220
The Bible teaches that God has given every believer, every follower of Jesus,

85
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:39,920
has been given at least one, if not more, spiritual gifts for the building up and the development

86
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:43,180
and the extension of the local church.

87
00:05:44,650 --> 00:05:47,450
For a quick review, we saw last week a great definition.

88
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:50,050
If you didn't get it, you might jot this down today.

89
00:05:50,050 --> 00:06:06,040
A spiritual gift is a special ability that God gives, according to His grace, to each member of the body of Christ to be used for the development of the church.

90
00:06:07,180 --> 00:06:10,340
To be used for the development of the church.

91
00:06:11,180 --> 00:06:15,460
It's not just for our own enjoyment, though that's a byproduct.

92
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:20,460
It's not just for our own fulfillment, though that happens to be true.

93
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:25,140
It's for the development of the body of Christ in the community.

94
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:29,060
Why does he do that?

95
00:06:29,870 --> 00:06:31,490
Why does God do it that way?

96
00:06:31,490 --> 00:06:35,970
Why does God give these gifts to his people to build up the church?

97
00:06:37,180 --> 00:06:39,980
And the deeper question is, well, what's so special about the church?

98
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:49,500
Because the church is God's vehicle for bringing God's kingdom to the world.

99
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:53,800
It's the way God grows the kingdom.

100
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:57,900
Through the church, lives are changed.

101
00:06:57,900 --> 00:07:02,280
People find forgiveness and wholeness and justice.

102
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:06,960
They find meaning and purpose and a call upon their lives.

103
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:10,080
They find a connection to God's people

104
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:15,320
and an intimate expression of the love in their hearts towards God.

105
00:07:16,820 --> 00:07:21,840
There is nothing in the world like the church when it's working right.

106
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:23,820
There's nothing like it.

107
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:28,600
And friends, there's nothing worth committing to with all of your heart, soul, and being

108
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,040
than the church when it's working right.

109
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:35,840
But you've also seen some churches not working right.

110
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:40,300
And they've got to work right for it really to be effective

111
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:42,540
in doing what God has called it to be about.

112
00:07:43,220 --> 00:07:46,600
And I believe at Fullerton First Baptist that we're all about being

113
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:50,520
the best expression of the local church that we can be.

114
00:07:51,410 --> 00:07:55,350
We're here to be the best that we can be for God's glory.

115
00:07:55,870 --> 00:08:00,330
We're here to run full tilt with all of our energy

116
00:08:00,330 --> 00:08:06,350
operating in the most effective, efficient, and wonderfully powered way that we can.

117
00:08:07,630 --> 00:08:09,930
And we're all excited about doing that.

118
00:08:09,930 --> 00:08:17,040
And the way we begin to do that is to discover what God has gifted us to do.

119
00:08:18,660 --> 00:08:21,400
That's heady stuff, but it's true.

120
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:26,740
and I believe that God wants to have you come along on this adventure.

121
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:29,620
He really wants you to grow in this area

122
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:33,160
and to step out in faith and experiment and try

123
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:35,680
and watch his power fill your life

124
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:39,600
and watch him change lives through you in this community.

125
00:08:40,380 --> 00:08:41,420
There's nothing like it.

126
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:42,680
Nothing like it.

127
00:08:44,590 --> 00:08:47,100
There's nothing like stepping back

128
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:49,600
from an opportunity where you've had

129
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:53,900
to step out in faith and use a gift he's given you

130
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:56,940
and watch somebody come and say,

131
00:08:57,420 --> 00:08:58,460
I was so blessed.

132
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:01,820
God spoke through you to me.

133
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:04,540
God brought you right into my life,

134
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:07,760
right at the moment when I needed thus and such,

135
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:10,820
and you came with your gift and blessed me.

136
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:13,880
There's nothing like hearing that the God of the universe

137
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:16,400
is using you to change lives.

138
00:09:17,350 --> 00:09:18,310
There's nothing like that.

139
00:09:19,180 --> 00:09:21,520
It's one of those Holy Ghost shivering kind of moments.

140
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:30,860
There are days when I will preach and you will say things to me that I didn't even know I said.

141
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:37,380
I had no idea that that thought that I wrote down two or three days ago, a week ago,

142
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:41,980
was going to slice right through your life and touch you in the most intimate way.

143
00:09:42,620 --> 00:09:43,640
I had no idea.

144
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:48,700
But what a blessing it is to walk away and realize God used me.

145
00:09:49,340 --> 00:09:52,520
That he used my study time to bless you.

146
00:09:53,290 --> 00:09:54,910
There is nothing like that.

147
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,640
I love that experience.

148
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,540
It keeps me going every time.

149
00:09:59,780 --> 00:10:03,440
Every Sunday morning I drive here and about halfway here I go, oh, Jesus.

150
00:10:04,540 --> 00:10:05,440
Here we go again.

151
00:10:06,540 --> 00:10:07,420
Use me, Lord.

152
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:13,860
I hope that what I have given you in my thinking and studying and writing is going to be used of you.

153
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:14,520
But you know what?

154
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:15,320
It's not about me.

155
00:10:15,380 --> 00:10:15,940
It's about you.

156
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:21,780
And then when you come and say thank you, it blesses me so much.

157
00:10:22,570 --> 00:10:24,630
That's because God is using my spiritual gifts.

158
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:27,500
And you may not have all the same gifts.

159
00:10:27,860 --> 00:10:35,340
In fact, we don't have all the same gifts, so we can do different things as a body together to operate together.

160
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:40,870
But there's nothing like it when you use your gift and somebody's blessed.

161
00:10:41,810 --> 00:10:44,180
Wow, that's why we're here.

162
00:10:45,180 --> 00:10:45,920
That's why we're here.

163
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:56,520
I want to share some scriptures that just elevate and document, if I can use that word, these spiritual gifts.

164
00:10:57,060 --> 00:10:58,460
To show you where they come from.

165
00:10:59,710 --> 00:11:00,730
Romans chapter 12.

166
00:11:01,330 --> 00:11:05,670
There are three basic lists in scripture where most of the gifts are located.

167
00:11:06,050 --> 00:11:08,010
There are some others in secondary places.

168
00:11:08,150 --> 00:11:15,130
But I wanted this morning to share with you the primary areas where the gifts are listed for your own study and your own thinking.

169
00:11:16,030 --> 00:11:17,330
Romans chapter 12.

170
00:11:19,390 --> 00:11:20,250
Starting in verse 3.

171
00:11:20,910 --> 00:11:21,470
Paul writes,

172
00:11:21,610 --> 00:11:25,930
As God's messenger, I give each of you this warning.

173
00:11:26,990 --> 00:11:30,150
Be honest in your estimate of yourselves,

174
00:11:31,130 --> 00:11:35,390
measuring your value by how much faith God has given you.

175
00:11:36,420 --> 00:11:38,960
Just as our bodies have many parts,

176
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:41,680
and each part has a special function,

177
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,980
so it is with Christ's body.

178
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:48,200
We are all parts of his one body,

179
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:51,520
and each of us has different work to do.

180
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,340
And since we are all one body in Christ,

181
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:57,660
we belong to each other

182
00:11:57,660 --> 00:12:00,680
and each of us needs all the others.

183
00:12:02,330 --> 00:12:03,890
God has given each of us

184
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:06,570
the ability to do certain things well.

185
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:10,440
So if God has given you the ability to prophesy,

186
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,660
speak out when you have faith

187
00:12:12,660 --> 00:12:14,180
that God is speaking through you.

188
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:17,180
If your gift is that of serving others,

189
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:19,060
serve them well.

190
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:23,680
If you are a teacher, do a good job of teaching.

191
00:12:24,790 --> 00:12:27,830
If your gift is to encourage others, do it.

192
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:32,180
If you have money, share it generously.

193
00:12:32,180 --> 00:12:39,230
If God has given you leadership ability, take the responsibility seriously.

194
00:12:40,530 --> 00:12:45,130
And if you have a gift for showing kindness to others, do it gladly.

195
00:12:47,310 --> 00:12:49,650
A number of spiritual gifts in that list.

196
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:56,760
The next major list comes from 1 Corinthians chapter 12, starting in verse 7.

197
00:12:58,680 --> 00:12:59,120
Paul writes,

198
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:06,340
A spiritual gift is given to each of us as a means of helping the entire church.

199
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:12,460
To one person, the Spirit gives the ability to give wise advice.

200
00:13:13,530 --> 00:13:16,490
To another, he gives the gift of special knowledge.

201
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,720
The Spirit gives special faith to another,

202
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:23,740
and to someone else, he gives the power to heal the sick.

203
00:13:24,580 --> 00:13:27,360
He gives one person the power to perform miracles

204
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:30,120
and to another the ability to prophesy.

205
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:33,940
He gives someone else the ability to know

206
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:35,760
whether it is really the Spirit of God

207
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:38,600
or another spirit that is speaking.

208
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:42,330
Still, another person is given the ability

209
00:13:42,330 --> 00:13:43,890
to speak in unknown languages

210
00:13:43,890 --> 00:13:46,210
and another is given the ability

211
00:13:46,210 --> 00:13:48,550
to interpret what is being said.

212
00:13:48,550 --> 00:13:54,290
It is the one and only Holy Spirit who distributes these gifts.

213
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:59,840
He alone decides which gift each person should have.

214
00:14:01,010 --> 00:14:01,970
It's not about us.

215
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:08,210
It's what the Lord gives, his desires, as he gives gifts liberally to the church.

216
00:14:09,730 --> 00:14:14,050
And finally, the last major list of gifts comes from Ephesians chapter 4.

217
00:14:17,530 --> 00:14:18,190
Paul writes,

218
00:14:18,850 --> 00:14:22,500
He is the one who gave these gifts to the church,

219
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:26,560
the apostles, the prophets, the evangelists,

220
00:14:26,860 --> 00:14:28,700
and the pastors and teachers.

221
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:34,960
Their responsibility is to equip God's people to do His work

222
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:38,060
and to build up the church, the body of Christ,

223
00:14:38,060 --> 00:14:43,300
until we come to such unity in our faith and knowledge of God's Son

224
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:47,800
that we will be mature and full-grown in the Lord,

225
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:52,060
measuring up to the full stature of Christ.

226
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:56,860
Then, we will no longer be like children,

227
00:14:57,640 --> 00:15:00,400
forever changing our minds about what we believe

228
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:03,420
because someone has told us something different

229
00:15:03,420 --> 00:15:07,080
or because someone has cleverly lied to us

230
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:09,900
and made the lie sound like the truth.

231
00:15:11,020 --> 00:15:14,480
Instead, we will hold to the truth in love,

232
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:18,460
becoming more and more in every way like Christ,

233
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:21,500
who is the head of the body, the church.

234
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:27,680
Under his direction, the whole body is fitted together perfectly

235
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:31,320
as each part does its own special work.

236
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:33,760
It helps the other parts to grow.

237
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:40,180
So the whole body is healthy and growing and full of love.

238
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:50,870
The point of spiritual gifts, that the church might be, and here they are again, healthy, growing, and full of love.

239
00:15:52,580 --> 00:15:53,240
Full of love.

240
00:15:56,740 --> 00:15:59,540
That's the point of studying the spiritual gifts.

241
00:16:00,770 --> 00:16:03,670
That the church might grow up and be mature.

242
00:16:04,210 --> 00:16:08,610
That we individually would grow up and be mature and full of love.

243
00:16:08,610 --> 00:16:12,070
and bring the kingdom of God to this earth

244
00:16:12,070 --> 00:16:16,050
and watch it transform lives, one life at a time, in the community.

245
00:16:18,030 --> 00:16:21,530
Now, in terms of these gifts, and I've shared with you three lists,

246
00:16:22,880 --> 00:16:24,800
there's other places in Scripture also,

247
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:27,200
and next week you'll get a chance to see a little more of those,

248
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:30,280
